{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/getweeknumberingyear()"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE20getWeekNumberingYearSiyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib8DateTimeC","extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"}],"title":"getWeekNumberingYear()","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"method"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/getWeekNumberingYear()"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"getWeekNumberingYear"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function, taken together with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_day_of_week()"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to determine the full ISO"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"week date on which ","type":"text"},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is usually equal to the normal Gregorian year (as returned by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_year()"},{"type":"text","text":"), except as detailed below:"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For Thursday, the week-numbering year is always equal to the usual","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year.  For other days, the number is such that every day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within a complete week (Monday to Sunday) is contained within the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same week-numbering year."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday occurring near the end of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one greater than the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring early in the next year)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Friday, Saturday and Sunday occurring near the start of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one less than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as the Thursday occurring late in the previous year).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An equivalent description is that the week-numbering year is equal to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the calendar year containing the majority of the days in the current","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"week (Monday to Sunday)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that January 1 0001 in the proleptic Gregorian calendar is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Monday, so this function never returns 0.","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/getWeekNumberingYear()":{"type":"topic","title":"getWeekNumberingYear()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/getweeknumberingyear()","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/getWeekNumberingYear()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"getWeekNumberingYear"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"type":"text","text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a single structure."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DateTime","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/G